<p>In <a href="/wiki/Computing" title="Computing">computing</a>, <b>platform virtualization</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Virtualization" title="Virtualization">virtualization</a> of <a href="/wiki/Computer" title="Computer">computers</a> or <a href="/wiki/Operating_system" title="Operating system">operating systems</a>. It hides the physical characteristics of computing platform from the users,<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> instead showing another <a href="/wiki/Abstract" title="Abstract">abstract</a>, <a href="/wiki/Emulated" title="Emulated" class="mw-redirect">emulated</a> computing platform.</p>
